Services


Research Help






Research Help
Here are some online research services and resources to get you started, and to help you along the way.





            Link Tiles top
          Heading link



 
Copy link









                            Use the UIC Library Search
                    

                Search for articles, books, news, events and more from the Library homepage.
            









                            Data management
                    

                Keep your research data accessible and intelligible during and after completion of your research project.
            









                            Visit Special Collections & University Archives
                    

                Two reading rooms are dedicated to researchers using our collections.
            









                            Get help with writing, style and citations
                    

                The UIC Library has resources to help you with writing, style and citations.
            









                            Data Management
                    

                Best practices for managing data, and resources for the UIC community
            









                            Copyright and Fair Use: Copyright Overview
                    

                A primer on the U.S. Copyright Act and Fair Use.
            









                            Contact a Librarian
                    

                Our Librarians can help you find articles for research papers, cite resources, remote Library access, and more.
            










            More Help
          Heading link



 
Copy link









